(to be undone by experience: An opinion dismantled by reality. An artifact torn apart by the) Tj
T*
(real world. An idea destroyed by its own shortsightedness. Experiencing these can be slow and) Tj
T*
(uncomfortable, but if you keep up your speed you can outrun them ? never reflecting on what) Tj
T*
(happened in your wake. Speed is how you avoid reckoning. It guarantees you miss things, and you) Tj
T*
(can?t learn from what you don?t notice. Wisdom?s feedback loop is slow. Wise people I?ve met) Tj
T*
(seem unhurried. I don?t think it?s because they?re slow thinkers or actors. I think it?s) Tj
T*
(because they?ve learned that important things take the time they take, no amount of urgency) Tj
T*
(changes that. Wisdom is chasing all of us, but we?re going too fast to notice what it?s trying) Tj
T*
(to teach us. Reply via: Email · Mastodon · Bluesky) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
